channel.title: Error - Help Please
channel.description:
Thats the error in the compiler that I get. I don't know whats wrong, can someone help?
[code]client.java:18321: talk2(java.lang.String,java.lang.String,int) in client cannot be applied to (java.lang.String,java.lang.String,java.lang.String,java.lang.String,int) talk2("This is DrugScape.", "It's probably the worst place to try", "*cough*", "and be productive, "+playerName+".", 0); ^ client.java:18330: talk(java.lang.String,int) in client cannot be applied to (java.lang.String,java.lang.String,int) talk("Well there are two things you can do...", "1. Smoke and get Drunk...", 0); ^ client.java:18333: talk(java.lang.String,int) in client cannot be applied to (java.lang.String,java.lang.String,int) talk("2. Try and be productive!", "You better hurry up! You're not getting any younger!", 0); ^ 3 errors Press any key to continue . . .[/code]

item.title: Error - Help Please
item.description:
@4_2_0 wrote:

Pretty self explanatory, you used to many strings.

You used 4 strings, and an int, when “talk2” can only hold 2 strings and an int.
